    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>May 30 1871</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am very much obliged to you for yr corrections.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> The name of the inhabitants of the Fiji I’s is spelt in in English many ways, &amp; this has been the cause of my blunder; I think Fijians is best.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> At vol 1 p. 29 the name I believe is Leguay.<ref target="#foot.f3"/> Many thanks about the horns; perhaps you will be so good as to insert the right numbers, viz. 33 to the left &amp; 27 to the right.<ref target="#foot.f4"/> It is a shame to give you so much trouble, especially as the Index has already cost you so much, but I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> be grateful for any corrections, as I suppose some day, I shall bring out a corrected edition.</p>
<p>I did not myself make the index &amp; the gentleman who made it &amp; made it too full, was much hurried at the close.<ref target="#foot.f5"/> Whenever you have occasion to write again, but do not write on purpose, I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> like to hear how many copies have been printed &amp; sold of your translation in Germany. In England 6500 have been printed.</p>
<p>Believe me with many thanks | yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.00 in English] <hi rend="italic">interl in CD’s hand</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">2.00 &amp; … full,] <hi rend="italic">interl in CD’s hand</hi> </note>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Carus had sent CD corrections for the German translation of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> (Carus trans. 1871). See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7774.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from J. V. Carus, 28 May 1871</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7774.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from J. V. Carus, 28 May 1871</ref> and n. 3.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_6144.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Louis Leguay</ref>. See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7774.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from J. V. Carus, 28 May 1871</ref> and n. 4.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7774.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from J. V. Carus, 28 May 1871</ref> and n. 5.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">The index to <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> was prepared by <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1179.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">William Sweetland Dallas</ref>. See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7438.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to R. F. Cooke, 12 January [1871]</ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
